laboratory_examinations.findings: Hepatic parenchyma appears within normal limits; liver contour smooth; no focal liver mass; main portal vein patent with hepatopetal flow; no ascites. Common bile duct mildly dilated (8 mm); cholelithiasis; gallbladder wall thickening and edema; edema within the gallbladder fossa; pancreas not well visualized; normal spleen (11.3 cm); no hydronephrosis in right kidney.
